                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(center)\">Duplicate</p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Pto Cabello</placeName>, <date>12<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >th</hi> February 1855</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Isaac Leeser Esq.</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p>Dear sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My last respects to you was on the <date>22<hi rend=\"sup\">nd</hi>\n                    Sep-<lb/>-tember</date> last, but I wrote you previously regarding our<lb/>\n                brethren in <placeName>Jerusalem</placeName>, stating that the few hebrews that<lb/>\n                are established here, showed a willingness in contributing<lb/> with their mite in\n                behalf of our above mentioned bre-<lb/>thren; but they waited the arrival from the\n                    <placeName>Interior</placeName>, of<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr David Lobo</persName>, to meet for the purport. I had to leave<lb/> for\n                    <placeName>Curaçao</placeName> as I have written you, and on my departure<lb/> I\n                requested an acquaintance that when the meeting took<lb/> place, he would oblige me\n                by including my name on the<lb/> list, for two pounds sterling. I returned here last\n                month<lb/> together with my family, and after having been here<lb/> for a few days,\n                I enquired whether any thing had been<lb/> done, and regret to say that the answer I\n                got, was<lb/> a negative.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The Calender you sent me was received here during<lb/> my absence,\n                but without any of your communication.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I enclose a draft on <persName>Messrs. Dallett\n                Brothers</persName><lb/> for twenty dollars. Please pay yourself for the\n                Cal-<lb/>ender, my contribution for the next year of your Occi-<lb/>dent, and for a\n                daily prayer book in hebrew and<lb/> german, that I will thank you to send me by\n                first<lb/> opportunity. The remainder is for our brethren in\n                    <placeName>Je<lb/>-rusalem</placeName>. Excuse the trifle: the french say: “On\n                fait ce<lb/> qu'on peut, et non pas ce qu' on veut.” If this trifling</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g44j98r/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
